{"schema":1,"kind":"decision","id":"01KX4AA5EER2KP6J0F2QW18FJP","title":"Use aggregate cmux rows for resource badges","decision":"Read only cmux's aggregate workspace rows when refreshing resource badges, preserve the existing tab metrics, and avoid writing a status again when its visible text and color are unchanged. This keeps the monitoring feature while reducing needless IPC, serialization, and terminal redraws.","alternatives":[{"option":"Process-tree scan on every refresh","why_rejected":"The badge parser only consumes workspace rows, while the current scan emits every child process and adds avoidable cmux work."},{"option":"Disable resource badges","why_rejected":"It would remove the per-workspace visibility the operator explicitly wants."}],"forcing":"Live diagnosis showed cmux and WindowServer are already consuming UI CPU; the guard must not amplify that load.","scope":["src/daemon/cmux.rs,src/daemon/guard.rs,README.md"],"commits":["79c36c2096d89915be3ee65e685830802d00c42f"],"author":"codex","confidence":"high","tags":["cmux,performance,badges"],"ts":1783630206414}
